[[File:AmyBergJul2011.jpg|thumb|right|Berg in July 2011]]
'''Amy Berg''' grew up in  [[Castro Valley]], [[California]], USA.  She is an American TV writer and showrunner, known best for her work on ''[[Counterpart (TV series)|Counterpart]]'', ''[[Da Vinci's Demons]]'', ''[[Person of Interest (TV series)|Person of Interest]]'', ''[[Eureka (U.S. TV series)|Eureka]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eurekaunscripted.typepad.com/blog/2010/01/about-us-amy-berg.html |title=Eureka Unscripted: About us: Amy Berg | accessdate=2011-01-07 |work= |publisher= |date= | archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20101122200313/http://eurekaunscripted.typepad.com/blog/2010/01/about-us-amy-berg.html| archivedate= 22 November 2010 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref> ''[[Leverage (TV series)|Leverage]]'',  and ''[[The 4400]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nicegirlstv.com/2010/12/29/spotlight-women-behind-the-scenes-amy-berg/ |title=Spotlight: Women Behind the Scenes: Amy Berg |accessdate=2011-09-29 |work= |publisher=Nicegirlstv.com |date=2010-12-29  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.buddytv.com/articles/2007-comicon/eureka-producer-amy-berg-talks-40959.aspx |title=Buddy TV Interview |accessdate=2011-08-07 |work= |publisher=BuddyTV.com |date= }}</ref> Her other television credits include ''[[Boomtown (2002 TV series)|Boomtown]]'' and ''[[Threshold (TV series)|Threshold]]''.  She was also a featured performer at [[w00tstock]] 3.0 during San Diego Comic Con in 2011. In September 2011, she made a guest appearance as herself in an episode of ''Eureka'' guest star [[Felicia Day]]'s web series ''[[The Guild (web series)|The Guild]]''. Similarly, in May 2013 she made a guest appearance as herself in an episode of ''Eureka'' and ''Leverage'' guest star [[Wil Wheaton]]'s web series ''[[Tabletop (web series)|TableTop]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1vbA7Bk6-pI&list=PL4F80C7D2DC8D9B6C&index=1 | title=Once Upon a Time}}</ref>

