{{Infobox musical artist | name = Kat Meoz | background = solo_singer | image = ChinatownSummerNights.jpg | caption = Meoz performing in September 2016 | birth_name = Katherine Alexandra Meoz | birth_place = [[Houston, Texas]], U.S. | instrument = Vocals, Guitar, Bass, Keys | years_active = 2003-Present | label = Bodan Kuma Recordings, AWAL | associated_acts = GRIT, Jennie Vee & The Garden of Eden, Iggy Azalea | website = {{URL|katmeoz.com}} }}
'''Katherine "Kat" Alexandra Meoz''' (born July 27, 1988) is a Venezuelan-American singer-songwriter, composer, soundtrack and record producer. As producer of the soundtrack [[The Dust Storm (2015 film)]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theduststormfilm.com|title=Home|website=The Dust Storm|language=en-US|access-date=2017-08-23}}</ref> she renewed interest in indie-rock music. Three of Meoz's original songs in the film were performed by actor [[Colin O'Donoghue]], [[Once Upon a Time (TV series)]]. [[File:Kat Meoz for Blackstar and D'Angelico Guitars.jpg|thumb|Kat Meoz is endorsed by Blackstar Amplification and D'Angelico Guitars]] As a vocalist and multi-instrumentalist, Meoz is best known as the founder and principal songwriter for the self-titled [[garage rock]] [[blues]] project, Kat Meoz<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/artist/kat-meoz/id441742523|title=Kat Meoz on Apple Music|website=iTunes|access-date=2017-08-23}}</ref>(f.k.a. GRIT). Her debut EP ''LA Don't Love You'' was released by indie label Bodan Kuma Recordings ([[The Subways]], EFG, Detroit Rebellion) in June 2017. The first official music video released was shot and directed by [[Troma Entertainment]] director [[Kansas Bowling]] in August 2017 for song ''LA Don't Love You''. The video and song which stars [[Lloyd Kaufman]] caught the attention of legendary radio DJ [[Rodney Bingenheimer]] who put the song in regular rotation on [[Sirius XM Holdings]] ([[Little Steven's Underground Garage]]). Meoz has received recognition from publications such as [[Nasty Gal]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://blog.nastygal.com/music/2016/09/grits-new-ep-salutes-anti-love-song/|title=GRIT's New EP Salutes the Anti-Love Song - Nasty Galaxy|date=2016-09-23|work=Nasty Galaxy|access-date=2017-08-23|language=en-US}}</ref> [[Impose (magazine)]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.imposemagazine.com/bytes/new-music/grit-new-car|title=GRIT, "New Car" - New Music - Impose Magazine|date=2016-09-07|work=Impose Magazine|access-date=2017-08-23|language=en-US}}</ref> [http://buzzbands.la Buzzbands LA],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://buzzbands.la/2016/04/13/ears-wide-open-grit/|title=Ears Wide Open: GRIT|last=13th|first=Kevin Bronson on April|last2=2016|date=2016-04-13|website=buzzbands.la|access-date=2017-08-23}}</ref> [https://www.grimygoods.com/tag/kat-meoz/ Grimy Goods] and is both a [[Blackstar Amplification]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://californiarocker.com/2017/01/19/blackstar-amps-swinghouse-party-namm/|title=Blackstar Amps Opens the NAMM Show With a True Rock and Roll Party at Swing House Studios|date=2017-01-19|website=California Rocker|access-date=2017-08-23}}</ref> and [[D'Angelico Guitars]] artist and was signed to [[Defend Music]] in late Spring 2018 for publishing.
== Career == The first ever televised composition from Meoz was the theme song for show [[Knock First]] which ran on [[Abc family]] for 6 episodes in its second season from 2003-2004.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm2536463/|title=Kat Meoz|website=IMDb|access-date=2017-08-23}}</ref> In 2016 and 2017 Meoz had three songs placed on reality television series the [[Bad Girls Club]]: ''Cold Blooded''<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BMAeGbCABP3/?taken-by=peteroriondavis|title=Instagram post by Peter Davis • Oct 26, 2016 at 1:16am UTC|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2017-08-23}}</ref>'', Fool's Gold''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BQgzx8_AwoF/?taken-by=peteroriondavis|title=Instagram post by Peter Davis • Feb 15, 2017 at 12:46am UTC|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2017-08-23}}</ref>'','' and ''LA Don't Love You''<ref name=":0" />''.''
In October 2017, filmmaker [[Kansas Bowling]] and Meoz shot the only existing footage of [[Richard Brautigan]]'s papier-mâché bird and subject of his book [[Willard and His Bowling Trophies]], Willard, for a music video for Meoz's song "Here I Wait".<ref>https://www.popmatters.com/kat-meoz-here-i-wait-2526591339.html</ref> The song was released January 2018 on Bodan Kuma Records and premiered on [https://www.popmatters.com/tag/kat-meoz Pop Matters].
In November 2017 Meoz was included on [[Rodney Bingenheimer]]'s Christmas Compilation, ''[https://www.amoeba.com/rodney-on-the-rock-presents-santa-s-got-a-gto-vol-2-lp-various-artists/albums/4004147/?code=ACEEdoTeiUw&gclid=EAIaIQobChMIm8_y1L7T2wIVRoF-Ch2o_wQIEAQYASABEgJ6vPD_BwE Santa's Got a GTO Vol.2].'' For which Meoz composed original Christmas song, ''Christmas in Hollywood''. The compilation, released on limited edition vinyl through [[Gearhead Records]] includes artists such as [[C. J. Ramone]] and [[Clem Burke]].
Meoz was asked by [[Jennie Vee]] to join her solo project: ''Jennie Vee & The Garden of Eden'' as a rhythm guitar player in early fall 2017, the act toured with Swedish band [[INVSN]] in California. In late December 2017 Meoz was asked to sing background vocals for [[Iggy Azalea]] and [[Quavo]] on the recording of their 2018 single release, [[Savior (Iggy Azalea song)|''Savior''.]] Meoz performed for their track at [[Westlake Recording Studios]] in Los Angeles. The song and Meoz's voice went on to be featured in a [[Super Bowl LII]] commercial for Monster Products' headphones. The commercial stars Azalea, [[Joe Perry (musician)]], [[RiceGum]], [[Yo Gotti]], and [[Joey Fatone]].
As an actress, Meoz was cast in a [[Motel 6]] [https://www.ispot.tv/brands/ded/motel-6 commercial] which began running nationally March 1, 2018.
